    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-01-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="166"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Taylor</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 13.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-01-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 14, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of December 19 (No. 23) has been
                    received. The President is gratified with the favorable reception which the
                    imperial government has accorded to Mr. Collins’s proposition for the privilege
                    of extending the Russian telegraph. We wait, however, the definitive disposition
                    of the subject which Prince Gortchacow has authorized you to expect.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bayard Taylor</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
